        <div n="935-174F" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="triplet"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-1"> By something form'd, I nothing am,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-2"> Yet ev'ry thing that you can name,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-3"> In no place have I ever been,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-4"> Yet ev'ry where I may be seen,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-5"> In all things false I'm always true,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-6"> I'm still the same, but ever new:</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-7"> Lifeless Lifes perfect form I wear,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-8"> Can show a Nose, Eye, tongue, &amp; Ear,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-9"> Yet neither smell, see, tast, or hear.</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-10"> All shapes &amp; features I can boast,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-11"> No flesh, nor bones, no blood, nor Ghost,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-12"> All Colours without paint putt on,</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-13"> And change like the Camelion;</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-14"> Swiftly I come, and enter there,</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-15"> Where not a chink letts in the Air,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-16"> Like thought I'm in a moment gone,</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-17"> Nor can I ever be alone;</l><l n="18" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-18"> All things on earth I imitate,</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-19"> Faster than Nature can create;</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-20"> Sometimes Imperial Robes I wear,</l><l n="21" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-21"> Anon in Beggars rags appear,</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-22"> A Giant now, and strait an Elf,</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-23"> I'm ev'ry One, but ne're my self.</l><l n="24" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-24"> Or Male, or female, yet my Sex</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-25"> No Naturalist could ever fix;</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-26"> Ne're sad, I mourn; ne're glad, rejoyce,</l><l n="27" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-27"> I move my lips yet want a Voyce</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-28"> I ne're was born, nor e're can dye,</l><l n="29" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-29"> Then, prithee tell me, who am I?</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="30" xml:id="spp-935-174F-line-30">Reflection in a Lookinglass.&#13;935-174F   </l></lg></div>
